Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugzra7pCXVUzE239iMJ4AaABAg,,@raymondwilson293,"Difficult movie to watch without context. Filmed during WWII before the outcome  of the war was certain. Many references that go unnoticed if you don't pay attention. One small one is the Cross of Lorraine and it's symbolism in the French resistance. You will miss a lot on your first view. I hope you take the time to watch it again. Another small aspect that most don't get is the story takes place in the days before the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor. Rick signs a receipt dated December 2, 1941 in the beginning of the film. There is so much in the movie. It is truly a classic.",2026-05-02T00:33:11Z,2026-05-02T00:33:11Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697924
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwaNiInwXihdIhbpuR4AaABAg,,@Billinois78,"While there are a lot of really, really good Humphrey Bogart movies, one of my favorites, besides Casablanca, is called Dark Passage. A good chunk of the movie is in first-person (POV), which makes it even more interesting.",2026-05-02T00:26:36Z,2026-05-02T00:26:36Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697928
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugygf2kj11Gq2g2ThhR4AaABAg,,@Billinois78,"Ingrid Bergman's 2 most famous roles are Casablanca and Gaslight, for which she won an Academy Award for Best Actress. 
It was also where the term ""gaslighting"" came from.",2026-05-02T00:23:34Z,2026-05-02T00:23:34Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697932
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwbomxpVDfVS4Id8pp4AaABAg,,@mainmac,"Casablanca is on of the greatest American films, and while it's not critically rated as the #1 film, it is without question the most influential film ever made with the American public, in bringing their support to the war, in how Americans as a whole saw themselves for well over a generation.",2026-05-02T00:17:33Z,2026-05-02T00:17:33Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697935
