Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugy3IzM-UdgsQU_jUEZ4AaABAg,,@MikeTaylorFAHS,"""Casablanca"" and ""The Maltese Falcon"" are two of my favorite Bogart movies... They had finished filming this movie and Bogart was across the street in a bar having a drink when the director asked him to come back to the set. All he wanted Bogart to do was look at the camera and nod his head. In the movie, that's when the band leader looks at him after Lazlo asks him to play Le Marseille.",2026-05-02T00:13:59Z,2026-05-02T00:13:59Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697941
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgxAyTnoIKZ7PxXw1Ll4AaABAg,,@steelers6titles,"In retrospect, the movie is utterly conventional; a product of Old Hollywood.  Based on an unproduced play, using songs which had been around awhile, and directed by an otherwise-unremarkable workhorse for the studio system, and featuring contract players (Bogart had broken through to stardom after years of gangsters for Jack L. Warner), it could be expected to be ordinary.  But somehow everything came together to create a great film, and it received acclaim from the beginning.",2026-05-02T00:08:40Z,2026-05-02T00:09:13Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697945
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugx3v3RjMLkVffdjuap4AaABAg,,@thomastimlin1724,"You did a  great job on this Becca....I often wonder how many times I have heard a school principal [school master] say ""Round up the usual suspects"" lol. I was a music  teacher...I think there a so many funny lines in this that may have gone over your head. The funniest line in the movie to me is Captain Renault: ""I am shocked! shocked to find there is gambling going on here""  Croupier: ""Your winnings sir.""  Captain: ""Oh, thank very much."" I have  read that back in the day when the film was new, the theater crowds laughed the loudest at that line. The  most riveting scene was Laslo shutting down the Nazis' singing with the French National Anthem...that scene  always sends chills up and down my spine. It's easy to feel that way once you know what bastards the  Nazis were, and in the new forms of them in the world today, still are. I'm 70, but still have  a soft spot in my heart for  British girls, it must be the  accent lol.😁",2026-05-02T00:04:20Z,2026-05-02T00:16:11Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697948
