Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgzqT8_9BD6ucjZJBMR4AaABAg,,@joelcampbell7100,"There are some very interesting things behind the scenes you need to know.  First off during the filming there were constant rewrites being done but most importantly the actors until the last day didn’t know the ending themselves.  That actually affected Ingrid Bergman and kept her from inadvertently favoring Victor over Rick or vice versa.  The other interesting thing which was hard to see in the way it was broken up was the conflict between the Germans singing a nationalist song but then being drowned out by Victor leading the French national anthem.  As you noticed the war was still raging and many of the extras and even some of the actors were actual refugees themselves.  That’s why there was such emotion sung in the French anthem.  One well remembered line was “Here’s looking at you kid” !! Also Ilsa never told Victor she loved him which she actually gave away in the early scene when she came back late to the Cafe to see Rick.
She told Rick throughout the film that she loved him.  Bogart is still considered one of the greatest male actors in Film History and Bergman also in her era was excellent.  I’ve never seen your reactions before and I enjoyed your reaction to this film which is considered to be the best or in the top five films ever made.  
Thank you and God bless you.
🙏🏻",2026-05-01T23:48:38Z,2026-05-01T23:48:38Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.697965
