Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugw00vr5EeTHGiATdvt4AaABAg,,@MarcosElMalo2,"I’ve got a very cynical alternative interpretation. Don’t get me wrong, I love this movie and the noble sensibilities. But if you’ve seen it as many times as I have, you start looking for other possible angles. Anyway, don’t read further if you don’t like cynicism mixed with your sex. 

This is a revenge story about a well endowed ladies’ man who made the mistake of falling in love. Rick heals his broken heart by making Ilsa fall in love with him, satisfying her in ways her husband can’t. Then he rejects her, throwing her back to her husband. He even lets the husband know that he had sex with Ilsa the night before right before they get on the plane. That must have been a very awkward ride to Lisbon! That would have been very hard for Victor. His wife (whom he has never satisfied sexually) is crying her eyes out because her lover broke up with her. What is he supposed to say?

“How are you going to keep them on the farm after they’ve seen Karl Hungus?” ~~ Dude, the Big Lebowski",2026-05-01T23:01:16Z,2026-05-01T23:01:16Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698016
