Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgyyKjXXbdFVrUuisS14AaABAg,,@captainkangaroo4301,"This movie is dear to my heart for a number of reasons. It was the movie my parents went to on their first date in 1943 shortly before my dad shipped out to fight in the European theatre. They married in 1947. 
Bergman is without peer as an actor. She won three Academy Awards, four Golden Globes, a Tony and multiple Emmys plus all of the European and Scandinavian awards. She was fluent in five languages and made movies in at least four languages. She is my all time favorite. Bogart like so many actors throughout the years struggled for more than a decade to make a living as an actor usually playing second fiddle to the likes of the great James Cagney. But he became one of Hollywoods biggest stars the last 15 years of his too short life. 
Young people without a knowledge of Europe during the war especially the free vs occupied areas and the symbols of French resistance often struggle to comprehend the details imbedded in this movie. But Casablanca is so well written and acted that its brilliance overcomes that.",2026-05-01T22:37:16Z,2026-05-01T22:37:16Z,10,False,1.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698031
