Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgyOs2vpBEUbSRubK5p4AaABAg,,@davidwilkins5932,"There’s a lot to be said for B&W when it’s well lit and well shot. It reduces things down to basic elements, whereas color often distracts with its literalness. There are some wonderful modern examples. Most were shot in color then desaturated, which isn’t quite the same as true B&W elements, but they’re still very striking. They’re worth seeking out. When filmmakers go to that effort, other aspects of the production are usually put together with equal care. On the other hand, color can be quite “mindless”.",2026-05-01T20:36:04Z,2026-05-01T20:36:04Z,5,False,1.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698153
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgxbnFqRGTNbixVvpsp4AaABAg,,@jean-paulaudette9246,"I credit Victor Lazlo for teaching me that people are allowed to behave as rational, compassionate adults in matters of the heart.  Before this, every example I had on the topic were explosive rage or suffocating depression or manic joy or some such, and those always seemed dishonest or performative or otherwise unrelatable to me.  He sort of gave me licence to be calm in the face of tragedy or triumph.",2026-05-01T20:34:28Z,2026-05-01T20:34:28Z,16,False,2.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698157
