Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugy2BzA7Z4UnYWT64DV4AaABAg,,@jackmessick2869,"In May 1940, Germany invaded France and occupied a large portion of France, including Paris, within a few days. The rest of France signed an armistice agreement with Germany and thus was allowed to continue as a nation. That country was nicknamed Vichy France because its capital was the city of Vichy. They were sympathetic to Germany during the war, and they held on to French Morocco, including Casablanca. However, there were rebels, called the Free French, who opposed the German occupation and Vichy France.

Of course nobody knew how or when the war was going to end is a mind-blowing thought.

The ""Battle of the Bands"" scene floored me on first watch. I was just thrilled when the Germans lost. ""In your face, N4zis!"" went through my mind. And the whole cinema applauded when Police Chief Renault told his minions to ""Round up the usual suspects!"" and Rick was safe.",2026-05-01T20:01:28Z,2026-05-01T20:01:28Z,10,False,1.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698171
