Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugy_RN_fekc1Y_wPWWN4AaABAg,,@thomasoa,"Bogart starred in two separate movies in 1942 where his name was Rick, the date of the story is before Pearl Harbor, and it costars two of his Maltese Falcon co-stars.

The forgotten one is not good. Across the Pacific is directed by John Huston, who directed The Maltese Falcon, but he script is a mes, and the portrayal of Japanese people has not aged well.

The co-stars he inherits from Falcon are Mary Astor and Sidney Greenstreet.

If you know Bogart primarily as Sam from The Maltese Falcon and Rick from Casablanca, it is very odd to hear Mary Astor call him Rick.",2026-05-01T19:27:58Z,2026-05-01T19:27:58Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698196
