Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgxHsHPRyn15fweBf8J4AaABAg,,@larky368,"23:30 ""Another Visa problem has come up."" This seemingly throwaway line is actually the turning point of the movie. You don't see it here but Renault immediately grooms himself. Later on, a young girl approaches Rick and asks him if Renault can be trusted at his word. She is the ""Visa problem."" She intends to let Renault have his way with her in exchange for two Visas. She doesn't want to do it but explains to Rick that she loves her husband so much that she is willing to do this horrible thing. This self-sacrifice touches Rick and he lets her husband win enough money to buy the Visa so that she doesn't have to debase herself.
After this, Rick's course is set.
And in the final scene Rick tells Laslo that Ilsa had sex with Rick only to get the letters. He knew that Laslo would forgive Ilsa for her act of self-sacrifice even though it was nothing of the sort.",2026-05-01T19:20:10Z,2026-05-01T19:47:41Z,9,False,2.0,2026-05-02T02:01:02.698204
