Marrakech,Zcu5Pz2x5Rs,UgyRGNv4fwRINHoxgm14AaABAg,,@OK-mb7cy,"I was in Morocco in April. As a Moroccan who has lived in the U.S. for over 35 years, I clearly noticed the changes taking place. There is a construction boom from Tangier all the way to Agadir and beyond.
What bothered me was the attitude of some Moroccans in Marrakech. I was disgusted by how they treat tourists—subservient toward Europeans, yet still guarded with fellow Moroccans. I hope that attitude changes soon.
During my trip, I rented a car and toured much of the northern half of the country, from Taroudant/Agadir to Tangier. Marrakech is the city that least represents Morocco; it has turned into a kind of Las Vegas of Morocco, lacking soul. I hope things change.",2026-05-01T21:52:56Z,2026-05-01T21:52:56Z,1,False,1.0,2026-05-02T02:01:42.444550
