AFCON,8NFTgffGOqA,UgwFWP-nEOnrF1yr1Il4AaABAg,,@AKDeh,"In the 1982 World Cup, Germany (then West Germany) and Austria played a group-stage match that became known as “The Disgrace of Gijón.”

Germany scored early.

That exact scoreline qualified both Germany and Austria.

After that goal, both teams stopped attacking and spent most of the match casually passing the ball around.

Algeria, who had already finished their matches and beaten Germany earlier in the group, was eliminated as a result.


No sanctions were imposed. Instead, FIFA changed the rules afterward so final group games would be played simultaneously.

