AFCON,8NFTgffGOqA,UgxxhUcJQ9IgQ_RRpwt4AaABAg,,@BabalySeck,"2021 Incident (COVID-19 Dispute):
Brazilian health officials invaded the pitch just minutes into the match to remove four Argentina players who allegedly violated COVID-19 quarantine rules after arriving from England.
Argentina's Reaction: The team walked off the field in protest against the intervention, and the match was later suspended. 

2023 Incident (Fan Violence):
Before the national anthems, violent clashes erupted in the stands between Brazilian police and Argentina fans, with police using batons against supporters.
Argentina's Reaction: Seeing their fans being attacked, Lionel Messi and the entire Argentina squad walked off the pitch in protest, refusing to play until the situation calmed down.
Resolution: After police cleared the Argentine fans and the situation de-escalated, the teams returned, and the game eventually started about 30 minutes late, with Argentina winning 1-0.",2026-01-22T17:44:49Z,2026-01-22T17:44:49Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-02T02:02:46.752649
